other_tests.findings: Lymphocytic pleocytosis, with 13 white cells and 749 red cells. Normal glucose level. Slightly elevated protein level and elevated IgG level with oligoclonal bands. Cytologic examination showed only lymphocytes, with no malignant cells.
No anti-GAD antibodies. Presence of anti-amphiphysin antibodies confirmed.
Good organization with no epileptiform activity.

other_tests.procedure_name: Fine-needle aspiration and core needle biopsy
other_tests.findings: Specimens contained large, atypical epithelial cells suggesting metastatic adenocarcinoma.
